The origin of the universe remains one of the most profound questions in modern physics. This article explores the Big Bang theory, the concept of singularity, and the subsequent expansion of space-time. By examining cosmic microwave background radiation and primordial nucleosynthesis, we aim to understand how a nearly infinite density transformed into the complex cosmos we observe today.

